TESDA TRAINERS METHODOLOGY - D5

FORSTERING AND PROMOTING A LEARNING CULTURE
-Fostering and promoting a learning culture means creating an environment where continous learning, improvement, and knowledge sharing are encouraged.

Key practices of the Trainer
-Encourage active participation and questioning
-Promote respect for ideas and diversity
-Provide constructive feedback
-Support continous improvement
-Create a safe and positive learning environment
-Model enthusiasm for learning




